---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import sharcCarlaDiagram from '../assets/sharc-carla.png';
import resultsTable from '../assets/table.png';

const withBase = (path) => {
	const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/?$/, '/');
	return `${base}${path.replace(/^\/+/, '')}`;
};

const projectLinks = [
	{ label: 'Paper', href: '#' },
];

const scenarios = [
	{
		title: 'Intersection Right-Turn',
		description:
			'Right turn through an intersection comparing fast and slow processor configurations, showing how latency affects path tracking through high curvature.',
		highVideo: withBase('/videos/Turning_250ps.mp4'),
		lowVideo: withBase('/videos/Turning_5ns.mp4'),
	},
	{
		title: 'Lead Vehicle Stop',
		description:
			'Front vehicle braking scenario showing how execution latency changes following and stopping behavior behind a decelerating vehicle.',
		highVideo: withBase('/videos/LeadVehicle_250ps.mp4'),
		lowVideo: withBase('/videos/LeadVehicle_5ns.mp4'),
	},
	{
		title: 'Pedestrian Crossing',
		description:
			'Pedestrian crossing scenario highlighting how delayed computation affects emergency braking and reaction timing.',
		highVideo: withBase('/videos/Pedestrian_250ps.mp4'),
		lowVideo: withBase('/videos/Pedestrian_5ns.mp4'),
	},
];
---

<Layout
	title="SHARC-Drive | Hardware-Aware Simulation for Real-Time Autonomous Driving"
	description="SHARC-Drive integrates SHARC with CARLA to study how processor-level computation latency affects autonomous driving performance."
>
	<main class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 py-10 sm:px-8">
		<section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl text-center">
			<h1 class="text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-950 sm:text-5xl">
				SHARC-Drive
			</h1>
			<p class="mt-4 text-lg text-zinc-700">
				Hardware-Aware Simulation for Real-Time Autonomous Driving
			</p>
			<div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3">
				{
					projectLinks.map((link) => (
						<a
							class="rounded-md border border-zinc-300 px-4 py-2 text-sm text-zinc-800 transition hover:bg-zinc-50"
							href={link.href}
						>
							{link.label}
						</a>
					))
				}
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="mx-auto mt-10 max-w-4xl">
			<div class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-zinc-300 bg-zinc-50">
				<video
					class="aspect-[16/9] w-full object-cover"
					src={withBase('/videos/Turning_250ps.mp4')}
					autoplay
					muted
					loop
					controls
					playsinline
					preload="auto"
					aria-label="SHARC-Drive teaser video"
				/>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section id="overview" class="mx-auto mt-14 max-w-4xl">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-950">Abstract</h2>
			<p class="mt-4 leading-8 text-zinc-700">
				Control algorithms for autonomous vehicles are designed assuming instantaneous computation, while processor
				architectures are optimized for generic workloads&mdash;neither discipline accounts for the other. When a controller
				runs on constrained embedded hardware, the computation time may exceed the control period, causing deadline misses
				that degrade performance and can compromise safety. We present a co-simulation framework that couples
				SHARC (Simulator for Hardware Architecture and Real-time Control) with the CARLA driving simulator to evaluate how
				hardware and controller design choices jointly affect closed-loop safety. The framework simulates the controller on a
				parameterized cycle-accurate processor model, producing realistic computation delays that feed back into a
				high-fidelity vehicle simulation. We evaluate controllers across different driving scenarios and processor
				configurations. Results show that the deadline miss rate depends highly on the hardware parameters and the controller,
				and a high miss rate causes collisions in safety-critical scenarios.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="mx-auto mt-12 max-w-4xl">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-950">Method Overview</h2>
			<div class="mt-5 overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-zinc-300 bg-zinc-50">
				<img src={sharcCarlaDiagram.src} alt="SHARC-Drive co-simulation framework diagram" class="w-full object-contain" />
			</div>
			<p class="mt-5 leading-8 text-zinc-700">
				SHARC-Drive couples three components in a closed loop.
				<strong>CARLA</strong> provides high-fidelity vehicle dynamics and urban driving environments.
				<strong>SHARC</strong> orchestrates the control loop with zero-order hold timing, tracking whether each
				controller computation meets its real-time deadline.
				<strong>Scarab</strong> executes the MPC controller binary on a parameterized cycle-accurate processor
				model&mdash;including pipeline, caches, and DRAM&mdash;producing realistic computation delays
				<em>&tau;<sub>k</sub></em> that feed back into the vehicle simulation.
				By varying the processor configuration, we can evaluate how hardware design choices affect closed-loop
				driving safety without fabricating physical hardware.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section id="scenarios" class="mt-12">
			<h2 class="mx-auto max-w-4xl text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-950">Qualitative Comparisons</h2>
			<p class="mx-auto mt-4 max-w-4xl leading-8 text-zinc-700">
				Each scenario is shown under two processor configurations: a fast setting where the controller meets every
				deadline, and a slow setting where most deadlines are missed. This highlights how computational latency
				changes qualitative driving behavior across safety-critical situations.
			</p>
			<div class="mt-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-x-4 gap-y-6 md:grid-cols-3">
				{
					scenarios.map((scenario) => (
						<div>
							<h3 class="mb-3 text-center text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-950">{scenario.title}</h3>
							<div class="space-y-3">
								<div class="relative overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-zinc-300 bg-zinc-50">
									<span class="absolute left-2 top-2 z-10 rounded bg-zinc-900/80 px-2 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-white">
										Fast Configuration
									</span>
									<video
										class="aspect-[16/9] w-full object-cover"
										src={scenario.highVideo}
										autoplay
										muted
										loop
										controls
										playsinline
										preload="auto"
										aria-label={`${scenario.title} — fast configuration`}
									/>
								</div>
								<div class="relative overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-zinc-300 bg-zinc-50">
									<span class="absolute left-2 top-2 z-10 rounded bg-zinc-900/80 px-2 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-white">
										Slow Configuration
									</span>
									<video
										class="aspect-[16/9] w-full object-cover"
										src={scenario.lowVideo}
										autoplay
										muted
										loop
										controls
										playsinline
										preload="auto"
										aria-label={`${scenario.title} — slow configuration`}
									/>
								</div>
							</div>
							<p class="mt-3 text-center text-sm leading-7 text-zinc-600">{scenario.description}</p>
						</div>
					))
				}
			</div>
		</section>

		<section id="results" class="mx-auto mt-12 max-w-4xl">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-950">Performance Results</h2>
			<div class="mt-5 overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-zinc-300 bg-zinc-50 p-4">
				<img src={resultsTable.src} alt="Performance metrics across driving scenarios and processor configurations" class="w-full object-contain" />
			</div>
			<p class="mt-4 leading-8 text-zinc-700">
				Metrics across driving scenarios and processor configurations. Miss rate <em>&rho;</em>: fraction of
				steps where the computation time <em>&tau;<sub>k</sub></em> exceeds the sample period <em>T</em>.
			</p>
			<ul class="mt-5 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 leading-8 text-zinc-700">
				<li>
					At the fastest processor configuration, the MPC controller meets every deadline
					(<em>&rho;</em>&nbsp;=&nbsp;0%) across all scenarios, with accurate tracking and no collisions.
				</li>
				<li>
					As the processor slows, 15&ndash;31% of steps incur deadline misses. Stale inputs are held via
					zero-order hold, causing increased tracking error (position RMSE rises from 0.33&nbsp;m to
					0.89&nbsp;m in the intersection turn).
				</li>
				<li>
					At the slowest configuration, over 95% of steps are deadline misses. The controller can rarely
					update its input, leading to collisions in both the lead-vehicle stop and pedestrian crossing
					scenarios, and large tracking errors in the intersection turn (position RMSE of 4.17&nbsp;m).
				</li>
			</ul>
		</section>

		<div class="pb-8"></div>
	</main>
</Layout>

<script>
	document.querySelectorAll('video').forEach((v) => {
		v.playbackRate = 0.75;
		v.addEventListener('loadeddata', () => {
			v.playbackRate = 0.75;
		});
		v.addEventListener('play', () => {
			v.playbackRate = 0.75;
		});
	});
</script>
